question: Tī chit ê chū-liāu lāi-bīn, ūi-choán kong-si siu-tóe siōng chē ê thê-miâ?
Tī 2006 nî í-āu tit-chióng ê game, in hām-kiat ê hō-chōe ê chóng-sò͘ sī kúi-ê?
Chiu chiah ūi chòe-li̍p chòe-li̍p, hō͘ Activision chhut-phín, hām WII phôe-tâi siōng ū ê game sī sèⁿ-miâ?
Tùi chit pái piáu-chāi ê nî-thâu lâi khuànn, chiàn-iānn ê iû-hì hē-thóng ê tàn-sûn-sèng (exclusivity) ê chhit-liû án-choáⁿ?
answer: Tsit pái ê chhit-liû sī iû-hì chiàn-iānn ê thàu-le̍k hē-thóng tùi chē-chē hē-thóng kàu tan-it hē-thóng ê piàn-huà. 2005, 2006, kap 2008 nî ê chiàn-iānn ('Ultimate Spider-Man', 'Flushed Away', 'Kung Fu Panda') lóng sī ū-tang chē-chē hē-thóng (chha-put-to 4 kàu 6 ê hē-thóng) ē-tàng chài-iōng. Put-kò, chit ê chhit-tâi lāi-bīn siāng sin ê chiàn-iānn, 2010 nî ê 'Limbo', i chiàn-iānn ê sî kan-tāi tan-it hē-thóng (X360), chha-put-to sī tāi-piáu tio̍h siâng sî-kan piáu-chāi ê piàn-huà, chiàn-iānn ê tàn-sûn-sèng khah tiōng-iàu.

question: Lāi-hô 2007 kap 2008 nî ê chè-liām, ū hō-chò PC chāi-té chhoā-thiah, kap ē sîng-chiap tit-chióng ê game ū kúi-ê?
Tī chia ê phiau-chu̍t tang-tiong, ū to-tsē chiáh-luí ê iûⁿ-á-kiò sī Activision (to̍k-ka he̍k-chiá sī ha̍p-chè) chhú-lí ê?
Nāi THQ kāi siâⁿ-lâi Double Fine Productions chiap, chiū ài 2005 nî ê chè-liông chiap chìn-chîan, chiū ēng THQ chhut-pán 'Psychonauts', chiū-án-ni hit nî THQ ū lōe-iông ê iûⁿ-chú sió-chiâⁿ-chē kiūⁿ?

Tī chit ê chu-liāu lāi-bīn, ū chi̍t ê chheng-chhó ê koan-hē bô, chi̍t ê iû-hì ê chè-chok-chiá sī tōa kong-si (chhin-chhiūⁿ Activision, EA, Capcom) hām iû-hì ê chiap-siū tit-chióng ê kòe-têng ū koan-hē bô, í-ki̍k sī to̍k-li̍p ê chè-chok-chiá (chhin-chhiūⁿ Double Fine, Playdead)?
answer: Chit ê chu-liāu bô chōaⁿ chheng-chhó ê koan-hē. Tōa chè-chok-chiá chhin-chhiūⁿ Activision ū tit-chióng ('Ultimate Spider-Man', 'Kung Fu Panda') hām tī ji̍t-chióng ('Bee Movie Game'). Tī kāng-khóan, Electronic Arts hām Capcom sī tī ji̍t-chióng. Put-kò, to̍k-li̍p hām sió-chè-chok-chiá mā ū chhut-hiān sêng-kong; D3 Publisher ū chi̍t ê tit-chióng ê 'Flushed Away' hām Playdead tit-chióng ê 'Limbo', chiâm-chiâm Double Fine hām Quantic Dream sī tī ji̍t-chióng. Chit chiáⁿ-bêng hām tōa khòaⁿ-chin ê chè-chok-chiá hām to̍k-li̍p ê chè-chok-chiá lóng sī ū pí-sài-la̍t, chiap-siū tit-chióng ê sêng-kong bô sī chi̍t-ê chē-chē khòaⁿ-chin kong-si ê to̍k-chúi.

question: Na-ni chiat-nî (33-tè) ê tsú-pài siâⁿ-chiáⁿ sīnn-chhiūⁿ-chāi siâⁿ-chiáⁿ, in-ūi siá 5 chióng tiān-chú iûnn-lú. Kî-thaⁿ ê chiat-nî tī chu-liāu tiong kan-na siá 2 kam-na 3 chióng, hō͘ 2005 nî ê sò͘-liōng khah-chē (khah-chē 67% pí siâⁿ-chiáⁿ-chē ê sò͘-liōng) sī chi̍t-ê bêng-hián ê bô-chiap-toāⁿ.
answer: The 2005 (33rd) ceremony is an outlier because it lists 5 games. All other years in the dataset list only 2 or 3 games, making the count for 2005 significantly higher (67% higher than the next highest count) and a clear deviation from the pattern of subsequent years.

question: Chit-ê kong-si ê miâ sī siáⁿ-mi̍h, i chham chi̍t ê kan-taⁿ chi̍t ê hông-tâi ê game tit-tio̍h chióng?
2007 niâ ê game lóng-chóng ū sōa-chē ê platform siâⁿ chhut-hiān?
